In article <rayvt-040594113311@dd311.comm.mot.com> rayvt@comm.mot.com (Ray Van Tassle) writes:
> (PLAIN xor KEY1 = CRYPT1)
> (PLAIN xor KEYA xor KEYB) = CRYPT2
>     This is just like the 1st case, with KEY1 == (KEYA xor KEYB) 

This is of course true, but (KEYA xor KEYB) will be less susceptible
to dictionary searches.  The double enscryption produces a key of the
same length, but one which may be harder to guess.

